  "steps_data": [
    {
      "key": "ai_1",
      "display_name": "output markdown",
      "connector_key": "ai",
      "action_key": "generic_ai",
      "input_config": {
        "control": "object",
        "value": {
          "user_prompt": {
            "control": "text",
            "value": "Context:\ndocument GL code below:\n ${steps.ai_6.response}\n\nLine items in request below: \n${steps.zip_1.price_detail.line_items}\n\nLine items in document below:\n${steps.ai_12.response.lineItems}\n\nFetch api data and the the only the most relevant documents on request ${steps.zip_1.id}. If there are multiple versions of the same document only select the most relevant one. Then perform data validation on this request and suggest correct values. Include fields: \nCategory\nSubcategory\nPayment terms\nPayment frequency\nStart date\nEnd date\nTotal price\nSubsidiary\n\nFor all fields besides the category, subcategory and total price fields, try to look for them on the PO change order namespace, and if you can't find them there, then use the request namespace. \n\nOutput:\n\"summary banner\"\n# Header:  \"Mismatch found\" or \"No mismatches found\" .\nBanner summary: if at least one mismatched field: \"Some fields in this request don't match the uploaded documents. Review and update them as needed.\" only if all fields match: \"The request details align with the uploaded documents\"\nDo not include anything else other than the banner summary and the table below\n\n\n\nHeader \"Fields validation\"\n\"These fields can be updated in one click using the document's suggested values\"\n\ncolumn 1: (no header)\nmatch icon: green, yellow, or red. (Green is no update is proposed, red if update is proposed, yellow if original value is not found and an update is proposed)\n\ncolumn 2: \"Field\"\n\ncolumn 3: \"Request\"\n\ncolumn 4: \"Suggested based on document\"\n\nOutput a row corresponding to each result from data validation. For \"Field\" column, pick from names \n(Category, Subcategory, Payment terms, Payment frequency, Start date, End date, total price, Subsidiary, Location)\nNot all names in that list needs a row. DO NOT output a row if you don't see a corresponding data validation entry for it even if that row is one of the original fields that data validation is done on.\nAdhere to the following guidelines:\n1. If no update is proposed for a field, output a green icon in column 1 and output the matching results in column 3 and 4. Output a red icon in column 1 if the original value exists and differs from the proposed value. Output a yellow icon in column 1 if the original value doesn't exist and there's a proposed value.\n2. for each row, create a citation from  its ent_ai_result and place them at the end of the last column. Do this regardless of if the row matches or not.\n3. For original value, if it's empty just output \"Not Found\"\n4. For suggested value, if it's empty just output \"Not Found\". And if an existing value exists but suggested value is empty treat it as suggesting to empty the field and output red icon in column 1. \n5. If the field is \"estimated_total_price_cents\", when displaying it, display the currency symbol then the total amount in dollars.\n6. If there's data source information from the data validation output, render the data source text under the \"Request\" column within the <subtext text=\"{data source information}\" tier=\"red\"> markdown tag\n\nAfter rendering this table, render a Data Validation Component only if there are mismatches found. \n\n collapsible Header: \"Justification\" brief reasoning for selection based on document \n-category\n-subcategory\n-gl account \n-Subsidiary\ninstructions\n-limit to 4 bullet points\n-limit each bulletpoint to one sentence\n\nHeader \"Fields validation\"\n\ncolumn 1: (no header)\nmatch icon: green, yellow, or red.\n\ncolumn 1: \"Field\"\n-Location (billing address)\n-PII Risk or data sharing\n-currency\n\ncolumn 2: \"Request\"\n\ncolumn 3: \"Document\"\n\nHeader \"Line items field validation\"\n\ncolumn 1: (no header)\nmatch icon: green, yellow, or red.\n\ncolumn 1: \"Line\"\n\n- \"Item\": check all line items in request and all line items in document to generate a non-repeated list. \n   -- only show specific item name\n   --  keep all unique line item, do not drop any\n- \"Request price\": show corresponding price in request. If not available, leave blank.\n- \"Document price\": show corresponding price (use prorated_amount if available) in document. If not available, leave blank. Must include citation: only apply citations to the document data. Do not hyperlink the text, only place an arrow link afterwards.\n- \"Suggested GL codes\": choose at most three corresponding GL code for the line item from  document GL codes, only show code and subcategory name in bullet list. If hard to decide exact GL code, choose at most two. Do not add anything else. \n\ncolumn 2: \"Request price\"\n\ncolumn 3: \"Document price\"\n\ncolumn 4: \"Suggested GL codes\"\n\n\n\n\n## Header: \"Documents used in analysis\" \nShow bullets: Filename of documents analyzed \nInclude citation, limit to to single citation per document. \nAdd in parentheses what the document is referenced on (e.g. Renewal, Original request, Master agreement, vendor record) \nFootnote (lighter text) \n\"If the documents listed here aren't what you expected, check that each one is correctly labeled with the right document type, then rerun the agent. Only PDF and docx files are supported.\"\n\ndocument data below:\n${steps.ai_3.response}\n\nrequest data below:\n${steps.ai_2.response}"
          },
          "tools": {
            "control": "multipicklist",
            "value": [
              "document",
              "zip_data"
            ]
          },
          "output_format": {
            "control": "picklist",
            "value": "markdown"
          },
