            "value": "Review the provided request data and the documents from request ID ${steps.zip_1.id}. \n\nYour task is to:\n1. Identify which attached document (e.g., invoice, quote, statement of work, order form, contract) is the most relevant match for the request data provided in the request data.\n2. Within that specific document, identify the exact item, tier, or service being purchased based on the request data. (Example: If the input data is for a \"Silver\" membership and the document lists Bronze, Silver, and Gold tiers, specify that the purchase is for the Silver tier).\n\nOutput the following:\n-boolean of if document was found\n- Document Name: [Name of the most relevant file]\n- Intended Purchase: [The specific tier, product, or service identified]\n-reason for decision\n\nConstraint: Do not make up documents or information. If no relevant document is found, state \"No relevant document found.\"\n\nNOTES:\nSome documents may include disclaimers such as “this is not a legal invoice.” These documents are still acceptable for reference if they contain billing information, pricing, or payment details.\n\nbelow is the request data:\n${steps.zip_1}"
